dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Swanage, solid and drift, sheet 343
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain (England and Wales) Great Britain. Ordnance Survey. Sheet 343 solid and drift. North Decimal Degree 50.533333. South Decimal Degree 50.4833. East Decimal Degree -1.6833. West Decimal Degree -2.0833. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depth is shown by contour interval. "Original Geological Survey on the one-inch scale, by H. W. Bristow, F.R.S. Published, on Sheet 16, Old Series, 1855. Resurveyed, on the six-inch scale, by C. Reid and A. Strahan, M. A. Published, With Drift, April 1895.".
